# Lumiere Pasterie Staff App — Cursor Context

## IMPORTANT: Read CONTEXT.md First
Always read `CONTEXT.md` in the repo root before making any changes. It is the single source of truth for:
- Full database schema (12 tables, every column and type)
- All 25+ API endpoints (method, path, roles, request/response shapes)
- Role permissions matrix (owner, bar_staff, kitchen_staff)
- Auth flow, Socket.IO events, file structure
- Known bugs and QA checklist

If CONTEXT.md conflicts with this file, CONTEXT.md wins.

## Project Overview
Internal operations app replacing WhatsApp for a bakery business (Lumiere Patisserie).

## Tech Stack
- Backend: Node + Express + TypeScript, deployed on Railway
- Database: PostgreSQL 18.3 on Railway
- Mobile: React Native 0.81 + Expo SDK 54 + expo-router v6 + TypeScript
- State: Zustand
- Auth: JWT (30-day expiry) stored in expo-secure-store
- Realtime: Socket.IO
- File uploads: Cloudinary
- Push: expo-server-sdk (backend) + expo-notifications (mobile)

## Live URLs
- Backend API: https://lumiere-staff-api-production.up.railway.app
- GitHub: https://github.com/HamesInFlames/lumiere-app

## Project Structure
- `backend/` — Node + Express API (fully built and deployed)
- `mobile/` — React Native + Expo app
- `CONTEXT.md` — Full developer reference (DB schema, API docs, etc.)

## Roles
- owner (Eliran) — full access to everything
- bar_staff — channels, orders, calendar, bar inventory
- kitchen_staff (Cat = Lumiere, Jade = Tova) — channels, orders (view + kitchen status only), kitchen inventory, recipes

## Coordination with Claude Code
Claude Code also works on this repo and pushes to main. To avoid conflicts:
- Always `git pull origin main` before starting work
- Check git log for recent Claude Code commits before editing files
- If Claude Code owns a file (recent commits), work in a NEW branch and create a PR
- Never force-push to main

## Rules
- Do not modify existing working code unless the prompt specifically asks for it
- Do not add dependencies without checking package.json first
- Always use TypeScript with proper types — no 'any' unless absolutely necessary
- Always use StyleSheet for React Native styles — no inline styles
- Always use the axios instance from `mobile/lib/api.ts` for API calls
- Double confirmation before any delete or destructive action in the UI
- Backend field names are snake_case everywhere — match them exactly
- users.id is INTEGER (SERIAL), all other IDs are UUID
- Always check CONTEXT.md for the exact API endpoint shape before calling it
- When fixing bugs, create a branch and PR — do not push directly to main

## Conventions
- Gold primary color: #8B6914
- Dark text: #1A1A1A
- Cream background: #FFFDF5
- Status colors: new=#FF7043, confirmed=#1976D2, in_preparation=#7B1FA2, prepared=#2E7D32, picked_up=#4CAF50, no_show=#E53935, cancelled=#9E9E9E
- Tab bar: Channels | Orders | Calendar | Inventory | Recipes (Calendar hidden for kitchen_staff)
- Settings accessed via header button, not tab
